---
/**
 * rest-api/0004 · Figure 1 — "Anatomy of a resource URI" (the hero).
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from docs/rest-api/lessons/0004-resource-modeling-and-uri-design.html
 * (figure + svg + figcaption). It lives as an .astro component, NOT inline in the
 * MDX, because MDX's JSX parser is unreliable with raw inline SVG that uses
 * kebab-case attributes (text-anchor, font-size, stroke-width, …). In an .astro
 * file the SVG is plain HTML, so it renders byte-for-byte.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 640 196"
        role="img"
        aria-label="Anatomy of a URI: /orders is the collection, 42 is the item id, items is a sub-collection, status=open is a filter"
    >
        <g font-family="ui-sans-serif,system-ui,sans-serif">
            <text
                x="320"
                y="20"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="12"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#111110">ANATOMY OF A RESOURCE URI</text
            >
            <text
                x="320"
                y="58"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="20"
                font-family="ui-monospace,SFMono-Regular,Menlo,monospace"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#111110"
                >/orders<tspan fill="#7a1f12">/42</tspan><tspan fill="#1f3a5a">/items</tspan><tspan
                    fill="#2f5d3a">?status=open</tspan
                ></text
            >
            <!-- collection -->
            <line x1="150" y1="68" x2="150" y2="92" stroke="#6b675f"></line>
            <rect x="58" y="92" width="184" height="40" rx="8" fill="#f1eee2" stroke="#6b675f"
            ></rect>
            <text
                x="150"
                y="109"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="10"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#111110">COLLECTION</text
            >
            <text x="150" y="124" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f"
                >plural noun · all orders</text
            >
            <!-- id -->
            <line x1="247" y1="68" x2="290" y2="148" stroke="#7a1f12"></line>
            <rect x="252" y="148" width="118" height="40" rx="8" fill="#f7ecea" stroke="#7a1f12"
            ></rect>
            <text
                x="311"
                y="165"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="10"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#7a1f12">ITEM ID</text
            >
            <text x="311" y="180" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f"
                >one order, by identity</text
            >
            <!-- sub-collection -->
            <line x1="300" y1="68" x2="430" y2="92" stroke="#1f3a5a"></line>
            <rect x="392" y="92" width="120" height="40" rx="8" fill="#eef2f5" stroke="#1f3a5a"
            ></rect>
            <text
                x="452"
                y="109"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="10"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#1f3a5a">SUB-COLLECTION</text
            >
            <text x="452" y="124" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f"
                >items of order 42</text
            >
            <!-- filter -->
            <line x1="430" y1="68" x2="540" y2="148" stroke="#2f5d3a"></line>
            <rect x="466" y="148" width="166" height="40" rx="8" fill="#eef5ee" stroke="#2f5d3a"
            ></rect>
            <text
                x="549"
                y="165"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="10"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#2f5d3a">FILTER · QUERY</text
            >
            <text x="549" y="180" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#244a2e"
                >narrows · never identity</text
            >
        </g>
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        The path segments name <strong>things</strong>; query params <strong
            >filter/sort/page</strong
        > — they never carry identity. The method (<code>GET</code>, <code>POST</code>, <code
            >PATCH</code
        >, <code>DELETE</code>) supplies the verb.
    </figcaption>
</figure>
